Namaste,
 
I have a word of caution regarding mental homam. If one with a w=
eak internal fire visualizes an internal homam, it will not be that effecti=
ve. Of course, it is safe to do and is better than sitting idle or watching=
 TV or other such activities. But homam in an external fire is more effecti=
ve for most people.
 
When we do homam, i.e. when we invoke a deity in fire=
 and make offerings while focusing the mind on sacred chants, essentially w=
e are trying to strengthen, by resonance, the fire that burns inside one, w=
hich transforms all of one's "experiences" into the underlying Truth. This =
is the fire that makes one experience deities and finally the Absolute. Jus=
t as a young scholar benefits from spending time with a teacher or a mentor=
 or a senior scholar, this internal fire benefits from spending time with a=
 good-sized external fire in which deities are invited and visualized.
 
* =
       *        *
 
Apart from this fundamental fire, there are so many spe=
cific fires in us. For example, jatharaagni (digestive fire) burns in the s=
tomach and digests food. Whenever you are eating, you are effectively perfo=
rming a homam in this fire. Of course, this fire is grosser than the above =
subtle fire that allows us to experience the Absolute. Nevertheless, it is =
fire too. Whenever you eat any food, you can chant a mantra and imagine tha=
t you are making the offering to god.
 
*        *        *
 
